  <summary>5/12/1998--Introduced.
Safe and Healthy Motherhood Act of 1998 - Amends title XXI (Children's Health Insurance) of the Social Security Act to authorize a State child health plan, under the State Children's Health Insurance Program, to provide for optional coverage of pregnancy-related assistance for targeted low-income, uninsured pregnant women.</summary>
